translate japanese intermission_e40b93af:

    # "Alright, let's move on!"
    "じゃ、次の課題に移ろう！"

# game/day1.rpy:795
translate japanese catcher_d0edf416:

    # p "Why don't we pick \"The Catcher in the Rye\"?"
    p "\"ライ麦畑でつかまえて\"はどう？"

# game/day1.rpy:799
translate japanese catcher_e297800d:

    # m "Whoa! Great choice!"
    m "うぉ！いいね！"

# game/day1.rpy:801
translate japanese catcher_538f7c1a:

    # m "This book is praised for a completely wrong reason."
    m "この本は高い評価されているが、評価されるところが違うと思う。"

# game/day1.rpy:803
translate japanese catcher_fa3a751e:

    # m "They say the book is famous for its themes of angst and alienation..."
    m "愁いと疎外感で有名な本なんだけど…"

# game/day1.rpy:805
translate japanese catcher_ea7e829a:

    # m "It's all made up by boring adults who don't understand \"The Catcher in the Rye\" at all."
    m "でも、それは全部\"ライ麦畑でつかまえて\"の意味がまったくわからないつまらない大人たちの勘違いだ。"

# game/day1.rpy:812
translate japanese catcher_64143785:

    # s "Marta, are you sure this is your {i}favorite{/i} book?"
    s "マルタ、そんなふうに言ってるとそれはマルタの{i}好きな本{/i}だとは言いにくい。"

# game/day1.rpy:815
translate japanese catcher_8e9914c3:

    # m "Look into my eyes!"
    m "私の目を見て！"

# game/day1.rpy:816
translate japanese catcher_a86b890a:

    # m "See? These eyes don't lie..."
    m "嘘をついているように見える？…"

# game/day1.rpy:817
translate japanese catcher_93c5da6c:

    # m "\"The Catcher in the Rye\" is my favorite book."
    m "\"ライ麦畑でつかまえて\"は私の一番好きな本だ。"

# game/day1.rpy:818
translate japanese catcher_133476a5:

    # m "I can relate to almost every phrase uttered by Holden! However..."
    m "ホールデンのセリフや気持ちをほぼ全部わかる。"

# game/day1.rpy:819
translate japanese catcher_941b194c:

    # m "Superficiality? Alienation? Who cares about that when you're sixteen?"
    m "疎外感？浅薄？16歳の若者にとってそんなことがどうでもいい！"

# game/day1.rpy:820
translate japanese catcher_af337ab5:

    # m "Certainly not Holden... Certainly not me."
    m "少なくとも、ホールデンにとってどうでもいいことだ…そして、私にとっても。"

# game/day1.rpy:821
translate japanese catcher_e2f231d3:

    # m "Holden is more annoyed by fake adults."
    m "ホールデンは建て前で嘘つきの大人が嫌がってるだけだ。"

# game/day1.rpy:822
translate japanese catcher_c27c5313:

    # m "The same fake adults who review this book."
    m "でも、結局そのような大人たちがこの本を評価してた。"

# game/day1.rpy:823
translate japanese catcher_d23c25ea:

    # m "Like, they say that Holden views the world as an evil and corrupt place..."
    m "ホールデンは世界が汚職と嫌悪にあふれているように見ているって…"

# game/day1.rpy:824
translate japanese catcher_f4d53f65:

    # m "Wrong, that's a point of view from an adult. J. D. Salinger was an adult..."
    m "違う！それは大人の視点だ。Ｊ．Ｄ．サリンジャーがそんな大人だった。"

# game/day1.rpy:825
translate japanese catcher_88657c1b:

    # m "That's why he did a poor job describing Holden's view of the world."
    m "だからホールデンの視点をうまく書き表すことができなかったの。"

# game/day1.rpy:826
translate japanese catcher_3e506b84:

    # m "Everything else is excellent, but often overlooked by critics."
    m "それ以外のことなら、本は素晴らしいが、評論家に買いかぶりすぎている。"

# game/day1.rpy:827
translate japanese catcher_be82f862:

    # m "I think this book should only be reviewed by young people."
    m "この本は大人ではなく、若者に評論されるべきだと思う。"

# game/day1.rpy:836
translate japanese catcher_a5a2f0ec:

    # n "Being an adult is tough..."
    n "大人って大変だろう…"

# game/day1.rpy:841
translate japanese catcher_3cd02cbc:

    # n "Imagine you wake up and, then all of a sudden you realized you turned 30 overnight!"
    n "ある日起きて30歳になったと想像してみて！"

# game/day1.rpy:845
translate japanese catcher_89aefaca:

    # t "C-could we... could we please get back to the book?"
    t "ちょっと…　本の話に戻ろう。"

# game/day1.rpy:855
translate japanese catcher_f0ad99b8:

    # s "So you think Holden finds other people stupid, Marta?"
    s "じゃ、マルタさん、ホールデンが他の人のことをバカだと思っているということ？"

# game/day1.rpy:862
translate japanese catcher_bd3c5fb3:

    # n "Not only Holden..."
    n "ホールデンだけではなくて…"

# game/day1.rpy:869
translate japanese catcher_e0b1fe32:

    # m "Well, kind of... and, you know, sometimes I can relate!"
    m "まあ、そうだとも言えるだろう…　本当は、私、ホールデンに賛成している！"

# game/day1.rpy:871
translate japanese catcher_3d0a910e:

    # m "Have you ever tried listening to small talk in the streets?"
    m "大人の間のおしゃべりを聞いたことある？"

# game/day1.rpy:876
translate japanese catcher_853631ec:

    # m "If not, try it... I bet you'll hear nothing but idle gossip."
    m "ないなら聞いてみて。ばかばかしいうわさ話しかしないよ、あの人たち。"

# game/day1.rpy:881
translate japanese catcher_1f50419a:

    # m "Moreover, people don't even listen to each other!"
    m "しかも、お互いを聞いてあげることすらしない！"

# game/day1.rpy:883
translate japanese catcher_54d77f1a:

    # m "They just take turns to whine..."
    m "ただ弱音を吐く順番を待っているだけ…"

# game/day1.rpy:890
translate japanese catcher_61ce8d84:

    # n "High five!"
    n "そうだそうだ！"

# game/day1.rpy:898
translate japanese catcher_f486196f:

    # s "But... isn't it exactly what Holden does all the time?"
    s "でもさ…　ホールデンもいつも弱音を吐いているじゃない？"

# game/day1.rpy:914
translate japanese catcher_dc283adb:

    # t "Let's wrap it up..."
    t "まとめよう…"

# game/day1.rpy:916
translate japanese catcher_a56ee6c8:

    # t "I think everyone becomes Holden at some point."
    t "人間はそれぞれいつかホールデンになる。"

# game/day1.rpy:918
translate japanese catcher_48ce5954:

    # t "However... maybe it's better not to stay like that forever."
    t "でも…　そんなホールデンでありつづけるのはよくないかもしれない。"

# game/day1.rpy:920
translate japanese catcher_bb2cdabb:

    # t "Holden said, \"I don't exactly know what I mean by that, but I mean it.\""
    t "ホールデンは\"これで何が言いたいのかわからないが、本気だ。\"といったことある。"

# game/day1.rpy:922
translate japanese catcher_480fbe35:

    # t "Look for your meaning in this book. It has multiple layers... like a cake."
    t "この本が言いたいことは山ほどある。さまざまな意義が重なって、ケーキみたいになっている。"

# game/day1.rpy:945
translate japanese crime_7007bd9c:

    # p "Why don't we pick \"Crime and Punishment\"?"
    p "\"罪と罰\"はどう？"

# game/day1.rpy:950
translate japanese crime_11657f94:

    # s "It's a favorite book of mine!"
    s "私の一番好きな本！"

# game/day1.rpy:953
translate japanese crime_b0bc306b:

    # s "It helps me to divide people into two big groups."
    s "この本を読んで、人間を二つのグループに分けることができるようになった。"

# game/day1.rpy:954
translate japanese crime_a2ee74d7:

    # s "They're really huge!"
    s "とても大きいグループだわ！"

# game/day1.rpy:955
translate japanese crime_fcd6d702:

    # s "Imagine you want to learn more about the person you just met."
    s "初めて会った人のことを知りたいときは…"

# game/day1.rpy:956
translate japanese crime_ebcb391c:

    # s "It can take quite some time, especially if you don't meet too often."
    s "めったに会わないと、人のことを知るまで時間がかかる。"

# game/day1.rpy:957
translate japanese crime_dbd0a277:

    # s "But there's a shortcut."
    s "しかし、近道がある。"

# game/day1.rpy:958
translate japanese crime_aefdfcac:

    # s "Just ask that person if they prefer Dostoevsky to Leo Tolstoy."
    s "その近道は、人にドストエフスキーかトルストイ、どちらが好きだと聞いておくこと。"

# game/day1.rpy:959
translate japanese crime_1a8175fd:

    # s "You see, Tolstoy portrays the world where horrible things happen to ordinary people."
    s "トルストイは普通の人々がひどい目に遭う世界を描いている一方で…"

# game/day1.rpy:960
translate japanese crime_765d4bf4:

    # s "Dostoevsky portrays the world where ordinary people do horrible things."
    s "ドストエフスキーは普通の人々がひどいことをする世界を描いている。"

# game/day1.rpy:961
translate japanese crime_31e50ba7:

    # s "Similar topics, entirely different approach."
    s "内容は似ているが、やりかたはまったく違う。"

# game/day1.rpy:962
translate japanese crime_f9248fdc:

    # s "That's why people who prefer one author to another might have a lot in common."
    s "だから同じ作家が好きな人は共通点がある可能性が高い。"

# game/day1.rpy:971
translate japanese crime_3822521a:

    # n "Sima, do you prefer ordinary people doing horrible things?"
    n "んじゃ、シマ、普通の人々がひどいことをするのを楽しむの？"

# game/day1.rpy:978
translate japanese crime_de23a181:

    # s "I admire strong, burning emotions inside people, that's all."
    s "私はただ人が感じている強い、燃えるような感情に憧れている。"

# game/day1.rpy:980
translate japanese crime_980d702e:

    # s "Maybe because I'm not that much of an emotional person myself."
    s "自分があまり感情的な人ではないからかもしれない。"

# game/day1.rpy:986
translate japanese crime_18c7e71d:

    # m "In my opinion, Tolstoy's characters are much more believable."
    m "トルストイのキャラクターのほうが信じやすいと思う。"

# game/day1.rpy:993
translate japanese crime_6add5413:

    # s "Trust me, Dostoevsky got to know a lot about people."
    s "ドストエフスキーがさまざまな人に出会って、人間の心を知っている人だよ。"

# game/day1.rpy:997
translate japanese crime_18e1e0da:

    # s "Not only did he work as a journalist and traveled a lot..."
    s "ジャーナリストの仕事をやっていただけではなく、旅行もたくさんしていて…"

# game/day1.rpy:999
translate japanese crime_902af653:

    # s "He also spent 4 years in a prison camp."
    s "捕虜収容所で4年間過ごしたし。"

# game/day1.rpy:1007
translate japanese crime_8b3c2d8f:

    # n "I can't stop thinking that Rodion's problems are created by himself."
    n "ラスコーリニコフが抱えた問題は全てラスコーリニコフが自分で作り出したのではないか？"

# game/day1.rpy:1011
translate japanese crime_1a0d6cca:

    # n "What stopped him from, say, getting a good job?"
    n "なんで就職しなかったんだろう？"

# game/day1.rpy:1015
translate japanese crime_5cbb7c58:

    # n "If I were a pawnbroker, I'd ask him to go be poor somewhere else."
    n "私が金貸しだったら、彼を説教する。"

# game/day1.rpy:1023
translate japanese crime_75c25bb5:

    # s "Well, Nana, I see you've read the book, but not carefully enough."
    s "なな、ちゃんと本を読まなかったように見える。"

# game/day1.rpy:1027
translate japanese crime_752d9609:

    # s "Rodion hates not only the fact that he has little..."
    s "ラスコーリニコフが嫌っていたのは自分がお金がないことだけではなくて…"

# game/day1.rpy:1031
translate japanese crime_8e281e96:

    # s "But also that a mere pawnbroker has {i}more{/i} than him, an able young man."
    s "あの金貸しが実力のある若者である彼よりお金を持っていたことよ。"

# game/day1.rpy:1035
translate japanese crime_28b68a63:

    # s "Rodion wanted the right to judge the value of human life."
    s "ラスコーリニコフは人の命の価値を判断する権利が欲しかった。"

# game/day1.rpy:1042
translate japanese crime_27886a6a:

    # n "The problem of inequality, right? Something that {i}communism{/i} tackles."
    n "不平等問題、ね？{i}共産主義{/i}の取り組み。"

# game/day1.rpy:1047
translate japanese crime_851ae2c8:

    # t "Class, let's stay away from politics, they are detrimental to your health."
    t "政治的なことを避けよう、みんな。政治は毒だ。"

# game/day1.rpy:1049
translate japanese crime_3d6fca39:

    # t "Anyway, thanks for your thoughts!"
    t "意見をありがとう！"

# game/day1.rpy:1051
translate japanese crime_2e40bfaa:

    # t "Both Tolstoy and Dostoevsky are, without a doubt, great authors and great minds."
    t "トルストイもドストエフスキーももちろん偉大な作家で、達人である。"

# game/day1.rpy:1053
translate japanese crime_b8b3e75e:

    # t "Maybe you can divide people into Dostoevsky and Tolstoy groups, but..."
    t "人をドストエフスキーとトルストイグループに分けてもいいが…"

# game/day1.rpy:1055
translate japanese crime_1b1bc0cc:

    # t "Please don't base your opinion solely on that, okay?"
    t "それだけで判断しないでください、ね？"

# game/day1.rpy:1082
translate japanese Winnie_70c0705e:

    # p "Why don't we pick \"Winnie-the-Pooh\"?"
    p "\"クマのプーさん\"はどう？"

# game/day1.rpy:1087
translate japanese Winnie_ef3ef168:

    # n "Yay, my favorite! It's the best book!"
    n "よっしゃ！私の好きな本だ！世界で一番いい本だろう！"

# game/day1.rpy:1091
translate japanese Winnie_4c19a8db:

    # m "Sure... {i}for kids{/i}."
    m "もちろん…{i}子供にとって{/i}"

# game/day1.rpy:1098
translate japanese Winnie_adb22311:

    # n "Marta, trust me, you're only scratching the surface!"
    n "マルタは表面だけで判断してるよ！"

# game/day1.rpy:1102
translate japanese Winnie_1b789f85:

    # n "Every character in this book represents a mental disorder!"
    n "この本のキャラクターがみんな精神病を表している！"

# game/day1.rpy:1107
translate japanese Winnie_209c2fbe:

    # s "I didn't expect anything less of you."
    s "さすがなな。"

# game/day1.rpy:1110
translate japanese Winnie_f440ccf9:

    # n "Can't you see the gap?"
    n "本当だよ！"

# game/day1.rpy:1111
translate japanese Winnie_b2c8bd94:

    # n "The gap in what they usually say about this book."
    n "あまり知られていないかもしれないけど…"

# game/day1.rpy:1112
translate japanese Winnie_8cc8745e:

    # n "Actually, it's a story about a boy who's very, very lonely."
    n "実はこれは孤独な少年の話だよ。"

# game/day1.rpy:1113
translate japanese Winnie_0dd641b8:

    # n "So lonely that his friends are all imaginary."
    n "想像上の友人しかいないほど孤独な少年の話。"

# game/day1.rpy:1114
translate japanese Winnie_18428435:

    # n "Although it's okay to imagine things as a child, this is a special case."
    n "幼いころの想像上の友人が一般的なことだけど、このケースだけが違う。"

# game/day1.rpy:1115
translate japanese Winnie_0405fbdb:

    # n "All characters are manifested depending on Christopher Robin's mood. {i}Schizophrenia.{/i}"
    n "キャラクターがみんなクリストファー・ロビンの感情を表している。{i}精神分裂症。{/i}"

# game/day1.rpy:1116
translate japanese Winnie_4bad3549:

    # n "Rabbit and Winnie-the-Pooh... Both are likely to have {i}obsessive compulsive disorder.{/i}"
    n "ラビットとプーさんは…　二人ともおそらく{i}強迫症。{/i}"

# game/day1.rpy:1117
translate japanese Winnie_89b04a62:

    # n "Eeyore? His bleak outlook on life could be indicative of {i}depressive disorder.{/i}"
    n "イーヨーは？彼の暗すぎるところがもしかしたら{i}うつ病{/i}の象徴。"

# game/day1.rpy:1118
translate japanese Winnie_09b74dd3:

    # n "Piglet's constant state of worry could mean {i}generalized anxiety disorder.{/i}"
    n "いつも動揺しているピグレットは{i}不安障害{/i}を表しているかもしれない。"

# game/day1.rpy:1119
translate japanese Winnie_98de2ee9:

    # n "And Tigger might have {i}attention deficit hyperactivity disorder.{/i}"
    n "そして、ティガーは{i}注意欠陥多動性障害（ＡＤＨＤ）{/i}だ。"

# game/day1.rpy:1120
translate japanese Winnie_9d5ec741:

    # n "I enjoy books with hidden messages!"
    n "裏側のある本が好き！"

# game/day1.rpy:1129
translate japanese Winnie_ca5e57b5:

    # m "Nana, I think you're... complicating things here."
    m "なな…　考えすぎだろう。"

# game/day1.rpy:1135
translate japanese Winnie_401028d4:

    # s "I'm amused how you turned a story about friendship into a dark and gloomy tale."
    s "よくも友情についての楽しいストーリを暗い悲話にしたな～。"

# game/day1.rpy:1143
translate japanese Winnie_831c990b:

    # n "You'll get it when you grow up."
    n "大人になったらきっとわかる。"

# game/day1.rpy:1150
translate japanese Winnie_c59f133f:

    # s "I wonder which character you mostly identify with, Nana."
    s "なな、どのキャラクターに一番共鳴している？"

# game/day1.rpy:1157
translate japanese Winnie_86a04326:

    # m "Nana is our Tigger."
    m "ティガーだろう？"

# game/day1.rpy:1163
translate japanese Winnie_2c1dabd2:

    # n "Who're you calling a Tigger?"
    n "誰がティガーだ！"

# game/day1.rpy:1165
translate japanese Winnie_5a18b7be:

    # n "And look who's talking, Miss Rabbit!"
    n "ラビットに言われたくない！"

# game/day1.rpy:1173
translate japanese Winnie_969351f3:

    # m "Okay, what about Sima?"
    m "んじゃ、シマは？"

# game/day1.rpy:1181
translate japanese Winnie_976c40d1:

    # n "Hmm... Piglet?"
    n "んー…　ピグレットかな？"

# game/day1.rpy:1188
translate japanese Winnie_30501c13:

    # m "The only Piglet here is you, Nana."
    m "ピグレットもななだろう。"

# game/day1.rpy:1196
translate japanese Winnie_768fb60b:

    # s "Maybe I'm too boring to properly represent a character, after all."
    s "もしかしたら私はつまらなすぎて、どのキャラクターにも似てないかも。"

# game/day1.rpy:1203
translate japanese Winnie_ea2ac1ac:

    # m "And who's our Christopher Robin?"
    m "なら、クリストファー・ロビンは？"

# game/day1.rpy:1210
translate japanese Winnie_5953b713:

    # s "Marta, it's inappropriate to joke about schizophrenia."
    s "マルタ、精神分裂症の冗談はやめたほうがいい。"

# game/day1.rpy:1218
translate japanese Winnie_c09d540c:

    # n "You know, I once heard that every fourth person has it."
    n "4人に1人が精神分裂症だと聞いたことある。"

# game/day1.rpy:1220
translate japanese Winnie_36d0b0d4:

    # n "So lucky it's not me."
    n "私ではなくてよかった。"

# game/day1.rpy:1227
translate japanese Winnie_5fcea445:

    # s "Me neither."
    s "私も。"

# game/day1.rpy:1234
translate japanese Winnie_8bf1bf85:

    # m "Same here."
    m "うん、私も。"

# game/day1.rpy:1248
translate japanese Winnie_289a19b1:

    # t "Ok, class, let's take it easy, shall we?"
    t "その話はやめよう。"

# game/day1.rpy:1250
translate japanese Winnie_a372cfbe:

    # t "It's up to you to decide what to see in \"Winnie-the-Pooh\": cuddly animals or mental illness."
    t "\"クマのプーさん\"は精神病の話かかわいい動物の話か、人によると思う。"

# game/day1.rpy:1252
translate japanese Winnie_0bcbd321:

    # t "By the way, Nana, you didn't say anything about the author, Alan Milne..."
    t "ちなみに、ななは作者のＡ．ミルンについて何も言わなかったね…"

# game/day1.rpy:1254
translate japanese Winnie_eb03e939:

    # t "Time often keeps the masterpiece but omits the name of its author."
    t "時間はしばしば傑作の作者の名前を捨ててしまう。"

# game/day1.rpy:1278
translate japanese lessonp2_50d0bff2:

    # t "Okay, class."
    t "じゃ、みんな。"

# game/day1.rpy:1280
translate japanese lessonp2_8d083696:

    # t "If you have any questions, now it's the time."
    t "質問があれば、聞いてください。"

# game/day1.rpy:1282
translate japanese lessonp2_a0919a0d:

    # p "What is your favorite book?"
    p "先生の好きな本は？"

# game/day1.rpy:1284
